I completely understand where brands are coming from and the need to manage budgets, especially when collaborating with creators. 

But when brands have already grown significantly and established themselves in the market, expecting creators to work on a barter basis alone isn’t fair. 

Makeup products won’t pay our bills — money does. We invest time, creativity, and effort into creating quality content, and that deserves to be valued appropriately. 

I’m not even charging a high amount; I’m simply asking for what is fair and genuine. Respecting a creator’s work with rightful compensation builds long-term, meaningful collaborations — not just one-sided deals.

♥️To fellow creators: know your worth. Exposure and barter don’t pay rent. If we don’t stand up for the value of our work, no one else will. Be professional, be respectful, but also be firm about what you deserve.
